main event: An observation of the planet Venus in Jacksonville, Florida, was reported on July 29, 1950, with the conclusion that it might have been a large weather observation balloon.
interesting points: The observation lasted several hours during daylight hours., The object was described as stationary and silent., Two jet planes passed underneath the observed object without incident., The investigation suggested that excessive time was spent without physical evidence., Multiple newspaper clippings regarding flying saucers over Jacksonville were included in the report.
sighted object: Venus or a weather observation balloon
witness description: Civilian observation of an object in the sky
